<Author>WeR2Travelers
<Content>Comfortable, Convenient, Full Service Hotel in a Great Location We booked and stayed in two double rooms (6 persons) at the Maria Cristina for the week following Christmas into the New Year. The practical rooms were comfortable and very clean, the staff friendly and helpful from top to bottom and the restaurant an excellent value. The concierge and other services were easy, useful and convenient. The location is safe and somewhat central. Each morning, after we left for sight seeing, the rooms were made up and 3 new bottles of water we left for us. Often, we encountered the cleaning staff in the hall and they made it clear (despite language barriers) they wanted to do the best job possible and wanted us to be totally satisfied with our stay. Half way through the stay, we had our laundry cleaned. It was done very well with small details attended to and all for a very fair price.Four times during our stay we ate in the restaurant - twice for breakfast and twice for dinner. The food was good (better than at least three other restaurants we ate in,) and the service exceptional. The waiters were friendly, tolerant of our broken Spanish, efficient and helpful. It was a comfortable restaurant and it offered a sizable, typical, and satisfying menu.The hotel offered a full range of services - which we employed during our stay - from concierge to hairstyling. Twice we asked for help arranging tours and were offered very reasonably priced and excellent private tours. We accepted both: one to Teotihuacan and one to Xochimilco. The former cost about $20 a person, the latter about $15 and both were complete, educational, comfortable and fun. On other occasions we asked for recommendations about restaurants, taxi rides and directions. Each time someone someone speaking English was able to help with advice, calls or specific directions. It should also be noted that I took advantage of the hair styling services and received a hair cut as good as any I have received in the US.The Maria Cristina is located in a good area. It is safe, has plenty of caf茅s, small stores and restaurants close by and sits one block for the Reforma (a large and elegant boulevard.) where there are even more conveniences. In addition, the hotel has a beautiful courtyard, comfortable lobby and fun bar for a little post touring relaxation.When it was time to leave the Maria Cristina, We were a little sad to be leaving a place where everyone was friendly and helpful and where we had become so comfortable. I am certain that next time we return to Mexico City, the Maria Cristina is the first place we will look into. 
