<Author>Zygmus
<Content>An Excellent Hotel in Mexico City We got a recommendation from the Conde Neste magazine, checked the Tripadvisor, and tried Maria Crisitina last week. The best hotel value pretty much anywhere in North America! Great location -- right off Reforma in Col. Cuahtemoc, close to all downtown attractions, across Reforma from Zona Rosa. Side street -- hence very quiet. Attractive surroundings, for an inexpensive urban hotel. Excellent service. New rooms -- ask for the newer part of the hotel with AC and all modern amenities. Big comfortable beds and everything nice and clean. Free valet parking -- and completely safe -- in the center of town!!! Internet available for a nominal fee. A very good traditional Mexican restaurant on premises. And the price -- the most expensive (non-suite) room: $73 (US). Overall -- a U.S. Hilton or Marriott standard at half the price. What else to you need? If you want to pay under $100 a night in Mexico City and stay at an excellent hotel -- go to Maria Cristina. 
